      "source":[
        "## Analysis of car market prices in India.\n",
        "For this project, we chose the dataset available at: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/nehalbirla/vehicle-dataset-from-cardekho?resource=download&select=Car+details+v3.csv\n",
        "\n",
        "The dataset contains information about used cars listed for sale on Cardekho.com. It consists of 8128 rows and 13 columns. It is frequently used for price prediction tasks, making it a good example of applying linear regression in machine learning.\n",
        "\n",
        "The main objective of the task is to examine the impact of various factors (number of owners, engine capacity, mileage, etc.) on the final selling price of cars in India.  \n",
        "\n",
        "The dataset contains the following variables:\n",
        "\n",
        "    name: Car name and model\n",
        "\n",
        "    year: Year the car was purchased\n",
        "\n",
        "    selling_price: Selling price of the car (target variable - this variable will act as the dependent variable)\n",
        "\n",
        "    km_driven: Number of kilometers driven\n",
        "\n",
        "    fuel: Fuel type (diesel, petrol, CNG, LPG)\n",
        "\n",
        "    seller_type: Seller type (individual, dealer)\n",
        "\n",
        "    transmission: Transmission type (manual, automatic)\n",
        "\n",
        "    owner: Number of previous owners\n",
        "\n",
        "    mileage: Mileage (fuel efficiency)\n",
        "\n",
        "    engine: Engine capacity (CC)\n",
        "\n",
        "    max_power: Engine max power (BHP)\n",
        "\n",
        "    torque: Torque\n",
        "\n",
        "    seats: Number of seats"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source":[
        "Numerical data: Columns such as 'year', 'selling_price', 'km_driven', and 'seats' are in numerical format.\n",
        "\n",
        "Text data: Columns 'name', 'fuel', 'seller_type', 'transmission', 'owner', 'mileage', 'engine', 'max_power', and 'torque' are in text format and require conversion to numerical format to perform statistical analysis.\n",
        "\n",
        "Missing values: The dataset contains missing values in the 'mileage', 'engine', 'max_power', and 'seats' columns, which account for about 3% of the data."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Dataset Preparation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source":[
        "%pip install --quiet matplotlib pandas numpy seaborn scikit-learn scipy\n",
        "# If using this file in Google Colab, you should delete this cell or not execute it, I am doing this in vscode"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "collapsed": true,
        "id": "qidZFKQFHcNL"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source":[
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "import re\n",
        "import datetime\n",
        "from matplotlib.ticker import FuncFormatter\n",
        "import scipy\n",
        "\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv('Car details v3.csv', delimiter=',')\n",
        "CURRENT_YEAR = datetime.date.today().year\n",
        "print(df.head(5))"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PiOSIUKYHXy2"
      },
      "source": [
        "Data cleaning - removing NaN values:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "collapsed": true,
        "id": "VsnXqwyhGG7J"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source":[
        "# checking data shape\n",
        "print(f\"Data shape before cleaning: {df.shape}\")\n",
        "# checking for NaNs\n",
        "print(df.isnull().sum())\n",
        "init_rows = len(df)\n",
        "\n",
        "# cleaning dataset columns\n",
        "df.dropna(subset=['selling_price', 'mileage', 'engine', 'max_power', 'torque', 'seats'], inplace=True)\n",
        "df.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)\n",
        "modded_rows = len(df)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\nRemoved {init_rows - modded_rows} rows due to NaNs in key columns.\")\n",
        "print(f\"\\nData shape after cleaning: {df.shape}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "bG8xkJH3JsXC"
      },
      "source": [
        "Conversion of specific units into numerical variables:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "WLaoYRLoGDMh"
      },
      "outputs":[],
      "source":[
        "# Mileage: Removing units and converting to float\n",
        "df['mileage'] = df['mileage'].astype(str).str.extract(r'(\\d+\\.?\\d*)').astype(float)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Engine: Removing \"CC\" and converting to float\n",
        "df['engine'] = df['engine'].astype(str).str.extract(r'(\\d+)').astype(float)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Max Power: Removing \"bhp\", handling empty strings/issues and converting to float.\n",
        "df['max_power'] = df['max_power'].astype(str).str.replace(r'\\s*bhp', '', regex=True)\n",
        "df['max_power'] = pd.to_numeric(df['max_power'], errors='coerce') # 'coerce' will turn non-numbers into NaN"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "XaO-tjJ-K9si"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source":[
        "# Torque: Extracting numerical value and standardizing units\n",
        "def clean_torque(torque_str):\n",
        "    if pd.isna(torque_str):\n",
        "        return np.nan\n",
        "    torque_str = str(torque_str).lower().strip()\n",
        "    val = np.nan\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Attempting to extract value and unit - regular expressions\n",
        "    match_nm_rpm = re.search(r'(\\d+\\.?\\d*)\\s*nm\\s*@\\s*([\\d,]+-?[\\d,]*)\\s*rpm', torque_str)\n",
        "    match_kgm_rpm = re.search(r'(\\d+\\.?\\d*)\\s*kgm\\s*@\\s*([\\d,]+-?[\\d,]*)\\s*rpm', torque_str)\n",
        "    match_nm_only = re.search(r'(\\d+\\.?\\d*)\\s*nm', torque_str) # For cases without RPM\n",
        "    match_kgm_only = re.search(r'(\\d+\\.?\\d*)\\s*kgm', torque_str) # For cases without RPM\n",
        "    match_num_first = re.search(r'^(\\d+\\.?\\d*)', torque_str) # Last resort, if only a number is at the beginning\n",
        "\n",
        "    if match_nm_rpm:\n",
        "        val = float(match_nm_rpm.group(1))\n",
        "    elif match_kgm_rpm:\n",
        "        val = float(match_kgm_rpm.group(1)) * 9.80665\n",
        "    elif match_nm_only:\n",
        "        val = float(match_nm_only.group(1))\n",
        "    elif match_kgm_only:\n",
        "        val = float(match_kgm_only.group(1)) * 9.80665\n",
        "    elif match_num_first: \n",
        "        # If it's just a number, we assume Nm, but this might be incorrect\n",
        "        # Let's check if it is \"number@number(kgm@rpm)\" - unusual format\n",
        "        weird_kgm_match = re.search(r'(\\d+\\.?\\d*)\\s*@\\s*[\\d,-]+\\s*\\(kgm@\\s*rpm\\)', torque_str)\n",
        "        if weird_kgm_match:\n",
        "            val = float(weird_kgm_match.group(1)) * 9.80665\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            val = float(match_num_first.group(1)) # Final assignment\n",
        "    return val\n",
        "\n",
        "df['torque'] = df['torque'].apply(clean_torque)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "collapsed": true,
        "id": "lgUqWerbLCcy"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source":[
        "# --- Step 4: Processing the `name` column ---\n",
        "df['brand'] = df['name'].apply(lambda x: x.split(' ')[0])\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Most frequent brands (top 10) and 'Other' ---\")\n",
        "top_brands = df['brand'].value_counts().nlargest(10).index\n",
        "df['brand'] = df['brand'].apply(lambda x: x if x in top_brands else 'Other')\n",
        "print(df['brand'].value_counts())\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dApotRrvLWLp"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source":[
        "# --- Step 5: Processing the `owner` column ---\n",
        "owner_map = {\n",
        "    'First Owner': 1,\n",
        "    'Second Owner': 2,\n",
        "    'Third Owner': 3,\n",
        "    'Fourth & Above Owner': 4,\n",
        "    'Test Drive Car': 0\n",
        "}\n",
        "df['owner'] = df['owner'].map(owner_map)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8cnjp3QqLi9I"
      },
      "source":[
        "One-Hot Encoding of the remaining categorical variables:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "srg2UQlZLbSJ"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source":[
        "# --- Step 6: Encoding remaining categorical variables ---\n",
        "categorical_cols_to_encode = ['fuel', 'seller_type', 'transmission', 'brand']\n",
        "df = pd.get_dummies(df, columns=categorical_cols_to_encode, drop_first=True, prefix=categorical_cols_to_encode)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "uG2PoS9SLn1s"
      },
      "outputs":[],
      "source":[
        "# --- Step 7: Creating a new feature `car_age` ---\n",
        "df['car_age'] = CURRENT_YEAR - df['year']"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "OGachzjKL08n"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source":[
        "# --- Step 8: Dropping unnecessary or already processed columns ---\n",
        "columns_to_drop_final = ['name', 'year']\n",
        "df.drop(columns=columns_to_drop_final, inplace=True)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "Hn_S9T9DL3tK"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source":[
        "# --- Step 9: Final check and NaN handling after transformations ---\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Number of missing values AFTER transformations and BEFORE final imputation ---\")\n",
        "print(df.isnull().sum())"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mrEbi0LRL9ig"
      },
      "source": [
        "Filling NaNs with intermediate values (median):"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "J3sBZ-91MCq9"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source":[
        "cols_to_impute_median_final = ['mileage', 'engine', 'max_power', 'torque', 'seats', 'owner']\n",
        "\n",
        "for col in cols_to_impute_median_final:\n",
        "    if col in df.columns and df[col].isnull().any():\n",
        "        median_val = df[col].median()\n",
        "        df[col].fillna(median_val, inplace=True)\n",
        "        print(f\"Imputed NaN in column '{col}' with median: {median_val}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Converting 'seats' to int, if possible and there are no NaNs left\n",
        "if 'seats' in df.columns and df['seats'].isnull().sum() == 0:\n",
        "    df['seats'] = df['seats'].astype(int)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "zGk05zdtMJJz"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source":[
        "print(\"\\n--- Number of missing values AFTER FINAL imputation ---\")\n",
        "print(df.isnull().sum())\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Dataset info after cleaning ---\")\n",
        "df.info()\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- First 5 rows of the cleaned dataset ---\")\n",
        "pd.set_option('display.max_columns', None)\n",
        "print(df.head())\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Descriptive statistics of the cleaned dataset ---\")\n",
        "print(df.describe())\n",
        "\n",
        "if df.isnull().all().any():\n",
        "    print(\"\\nWARNING: There are columns containing only NaN values!\")\n",
        "    print(df.isnull().all()[df.isnull().all()])\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"\\nNo columns containing only NaNs.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Final data shape: ---\", df.shape)\n",
        "cleaned_df = df\n",
        "print(\"\\nCleaning completed. Data is ready for further analysis.\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source":[
        "In summary:\n",
        "1. Rows with missing values in key columns were removed.\n",
        "2. Columns `mileage`, `engine`, `max_power`, and `torque` were standardized and converted to numeric types.\n",
        "3. One-Hot Encoding was applied to categorical variables (`fuel`, `seller_type`, `transmission`, `brand`) so they could be used in the model.\n",
        "4. A new feature `car_age` was created for better interpretation of age's impact on price.\n",
        "5. The few remaining missing values were filled with the median to avoid losing observations.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "0jlny8J0MtL-"
      },
      "source":[
        "# Descriptive statistics of the dataset:"
