        "The histogram confirms that the vast majority of cars are priced in the low range, probably below 1,000,000 INR. As the price increases, the number of cars drops sharply. One can also spot the presence of higher-end brands, whose price oscillates between 2,000,000 and 6,000,000 INR. Just like the box plot, the histogram clearly shows that the distribution is strongly positively skewed. In the context of prices, this is completely natural - most products on the market are affordable, and luxury products are rare.\n",
